<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="24" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,1113]" pageId="6" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,313,836,860]" pageId="6" pageNumber="24">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new species is somewhat similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Becker, 1911" authorityName="Becker" authorityYear="1911" box="[771,1186,836,860]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Chlorops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="canaliculatus">
<emphasis box="[771,1032,836,860]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="24">Chlorops canaliculatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Becker" box="[1039,1186,836,860]" pageId="6" pageNumber="24" refString="Becker, T. (1911) Chloropidae. Eine monographische Studie. III. Die indoaustralische Region. Annales Historico-Naturales Musei Nationalis Hungarici, 9, 35 - 170." type="journal article" year="1911">
Becker, 
<number box="[1131,1186,836,860]" pageId="6" pageNumber="24" value="1911.0">1911</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1254,1321,836,860]" name="China" pageId="6" pageNumber="24">China</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingCountry box="[1336,1424,836,860]" name="Taiwan" pageId="6" pageNumber="24">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
), 
<collectingCountry box="[151,218,872,895]" name="Japan" pageId="6" pageNumber="24">Japan</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[275,401,871,895]" name="Philippines" pageId="6" pageNumber="24">Philippines</collectingCountry>
in the ocellar triangle dark brown entirely, smooth; the 
<number box="[1020,1032,871,895]" pageId="6" pageNumber="24" value="3.0">3</number>
rd antennal segment blackish brown dorsally and distally, yellow ventrally and basally; and the palpus yellow. But it can be separated from the latter by the ocellar triangle with a black medial sulcus from the ocellar tubercle to the anterior margin of the frons; and the pregonite longer than the gonostylus, connected with the hypandrium in 
<number box="[977,991,980,1004]" pageId="6" pageNumber="24" value="2.0">2</number>
points. In 
<taxonomicName authority="Becker" authorityName="Becker" box="[1115,1389,980,1004]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Chlorops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="canaliculatus">
<emphasis box="[1115,1300,980,1004]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="24">C. canaliculatus</emphasis>
Becker
</taxonomicName>
, the ocellar triangle has no distinct medial sulcus in front of the ocellar tubercle; and the pregonite is shorter than the gonostylus, and connected with the hypandrium in 
<number box="[723,737,1052,1076]" pageId="6" pageNumber="24" value="1.0">1</number>
point (
<bibRefCitation author="Kanmiya" box="[816,995,1052,1076]" pageId="6" pageNumber="24" refString="Kanmiya, K. (1978) Notes on the genus Chlorops Meigen (Diptera, Chloropidae) from Japan and Formosa. Kontyu, 46 (1), 52 - 76." type="journal article" year="1978">
Kanmiya, 
<number box="[935,995,1052,1076]" pageId="6" pageNumber="24" value="1978.0">1978</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[197,1033,1087,1113]" pageId="6" pageNumber="24" type="etymology">
